.TH SQUASH-IDE 1 "2026-04-18" "squash-ide" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
squash-ide \- terminal task dispatcher for vault-based agentic workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B squash-ide
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B squash-ide
.I subcommand
.RI [ options "] [" args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B squash-ide
reads Obsidian-style task files (with YAML frontmatter) from a vault
directory and provides a TUI dashboard plus CLI subcommands. Selecting
a task in the TUI creates a fresh git worktree and dispatches
.B claude
with the
.B /implement
skill into a new tmux pane tiled beside the TUI.
.PP
When invoked with no arguments and tmux is available,
.B squash-ide
bootstraps a tmux session named
.I squash-ide
and runs the TUI in a left-pinned pane. Task panes spawn to the right
and share the remaining width equally. This is the default daily
surface \(em one terminal window, many task panes.
.PP
Pass
.B --no-tmux
to fall back to the one-OS-window-per-spawn workflow, or set
.B tmux.enabled: false
in the config file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --vault \fIPATH\fR
Path to the Obsidian vault. Overrides config file and env.
.TP
.B --terminal \fICMD\fR
Terminal emulator command used when
.B --no-tmux
is active.
.TP
.B --spawn-cmd \fICMD\fR
Command to run inside each spawned terminal or tmux pane. Default is
.BR claude .
.TP
.B --no-tmux
Disable tmux tiled-pane mode; spawn each task in its own OS terminal
window instead.
.TP
.B --tui-width \fIN\fR
Fixed width (cols) for the TUI pane in tmux mode. Default is 60.
.TP
.B --min-pane-width \fIN\fR
Minimum width (cols) per spawned tmux pane; spawn is rejected if a new
pane would force any peer below this floor. Default is 80.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Print the version string and exit.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Print help for the root command or a subcommand.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B list
Print tasks from the vault as JSON. Accepts
.BI --status\  backlog|active|blocked|archive
to filter.
.TP
.B spawn \fITASK-ID\fR
Create a git worktree on
.IR feat/TASK-ID-<slug>\  off\  origin/main ,
move the task from
.I backlog/
to
.IR active/ ,
update
.I tasks/board.md
and
.IR wiki/log.md ,
and dispatch
.BR claude .
Pass
.B --dry-run
to preview the actions without executing.
.TP
.B complete \fITASK-ID\fR
Archive an active task: remove its worktree, stamp
.B status: done
and
.B completed: <today>
in the frontmatter, update the board and log.
.TP
.B block \fITASK-ID\fR \fB--reason\fR \fIREASON\fR
Move an active task to
.I blocked/
with a one-line reason appended to the task body. The worktree is
retained so work can resume when unblocked.
.TP
.B config
Print the resolved configuration with provenance annotations
(default, config file, env var, flag) per field.
.TP
.B worktree clean \fITASK-ID\fR \fR[\fB--deactivate\fR]
Force-remove a task's worktree directory and local branch. Refuses on
active tasks unless
.B --deactivate
is passed, in which case the task is sent back to the backlog and the
tmux pane is torn down.
.TP
.B worktree adopt \fITASK-ID\fR
Re-register an orphan worktree directory via
.BR "git worktree repair" .
.TP
.B status \fISTATE\fR \fR[\fIMESSAGE\fR]
Shell-invocable status writer used by Claude Code hooks to update the
TUI badge when a permission dialog is showing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/squash-ide/config.yaml
Default configuration file. Override with
.B --vault
and other flags, or with
.BR SQUASH_VAULT ,
.BR SQUASH_TERMINAL ,
.B SQUASH_SPAWN_CMD
environment variables.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/squash-ide/examples/config.yaml
Example configuration file bundled with the package.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SQUASH_VAULT
Vault directory path (overrides config file).
.TP
.B SQUASH_TERMINAL
Terminal emulator command (overrides config file).
.TP
.B SQUASH_SPAWN_CMD
Command to run inside the spawned terminal (overrides config file).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmux (1),
.BR git (1),
.BR claude (1).
.SH AUTHOR
squash-box <https://github.com/squash-box/squash-ide>.
